{
  "text": "The 32 P-ATP-induced destruction of tumor parenchyma is due to two physical properties of 32 P-ATP, the spatial extension and the temporal duration of its beta-emission. With regard to the spatial extension, 32 P-ATP acts at a distance since the range of electrons emitted by 32 P-ATP has a length of 5 mm in tissues [CITATION_1] .",
